page.title: 11DUNKESWICK
page.content: Dunkeswick is a small hamlet with a few houses on both sides of a narrow country lane.There are 3 small cottages with tiny gardens,each separated by low hedges.One cottage has its door at the side of the house and a vegetable patch at the back. Another cottage has its front door directly onto the road.The door bell is a metal pole with a handle to pull. There is a pig farm.From the gateway can be seen stone buildings with broken wooden doors.Another farm has a long driveway,a large lawned garden, out-houses to one side and otherwise surrounded by fields. There are very few people about during the daytime,most inhabitants being at school or at work in Leeds,Harrogate or Bradford.
